User Story

Implement a caesar cipher that takes in a string and the shift factor and then outputs the modified string:

  > caesar_cipher("What a string!", 5)
  => "Bmfy f xywnsl!"

  get user input with gets
  split string to array
  convert each item to ASCII equivalent plus shift value
  save in new array
  convert new array back to string with join

  A-Z = 65-90 decimal
  a-z = 97-122 decimal

  ex Z =90
  90+5 =95 
  Z shoube be E or 69
  95-26 = 69
  so 
  if ('A'..'Z') === e
    if e + n is bigger than 90, subtract 26 from total
  elsif ('a'..'z') === e
  